name: The Canteen by Enjoy
description: Serves Mod Sin cuisine that Singaporeans will go 'Wah Shiok'. ENJOY was started in 2018 as a small eating house in Jln Besar founded by two childhood friends.
accept pre-orders: Order via foodpanda, deliveroo or phone @ 92991601

name: East Treasure Speciality Prawn Noodle
description: Offers fried Hokkien Mee as well as prawn noodles with two distinct flavours—local and Penang style.Hearty broth with umami and freshest ingredients.
accept pre-orders: Order via foodpanda, deliveroo or phone @ 62477545

name: THE NEIGHBOURWOK
description: Located in the heartlands of Bukit Batok, The Neighbourwok has a mission to serve great food to the community.

name: Hainan Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee
description: Operated by an elderly couple with a 60 plus year old recipe. Noodles and thin bee hoon are fried along with the stock until they completely absorb the whole flavour.

name: Shiok Hokkien Mee Golden Mile
description: Run by new generation of hawkers with multiple outlets islandwide. Thin bee hoon version, Pork lard upon request.

name: Nam Sing Hokkien Fried Mee
description: This stall has been serving just one item since opening its doors in 1960 – Hokkien fried mee with prawns. The  noodles and thin bee hoon are tossed in a rich broth made with prawn shells and tomalley to impart deep umami.

name: Yong Heng Fried Squid Prawn Mee
description: The Hokkien mee here leaned towards the drier, stickier side, served with sweet sambal. The gravy had a fairly discernible seafood sweetness, but unfortunately lacked wok hei.

name: 777 Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee
description: Despite its unassuming appearance, the dish had a pronounced wok hei lent not only by the wok-kissed egg bits but also by the tasty zhup.

name: Prawnography Novena Gardens
description: They use the same prawn broth which is also used for their prawn mee soup to braise the noodles. This results in a gravy which is very flavourful

name: Bao Er Cafe
description: Bao Er Cafe is a hole-in-wall local eatery in Balestier Plaza that serves up tasty kaya toasts and wok hei-rich Hokkien mee.

name: Shiok Hokkien Mee Tiong Bahru
description: Shiok Hokkien Mee serves up the ultimate plate of wok hei perfection. The smoky flavor, rich seafood broth, and addictive umami punch keeps everyone coming back for more.

name: Hong Heng Fried Sotong Prawn Mee
description: Michelin Bib Gourmand award-winner for multiple years. Decent plate of old school Hokkien Mee though some felt was overrated.

name: Come Daily Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee
description: Most favourite Hokkien Mee among Hokkien Mee Hunting FB fans, moist, flavourful, topped with pork lard fried fresh daily.

name: Kim Keat Hokkien Mee
description: Kim Keat Hokkien Mee sells something you don't see everyday — Hokkien mee served in a claypot with sharing portions going up to 6 pax.
accept pre-orders: Pre-order via foodpanda, deliveroo or phone @ 90114400

name: Kim's Famous Fried Hokkien Prawn Mee
description: Used to be helmed by legendary Rolex uncle. Quality of Hokkien Mee is said to have deteriorated.

name: Swee Guan Hokkien Mee
description: One of the favourites among Hokkien Mee Hunting FB fans. Smoky wok hei from the use of charcoal fire, portions may be smaller than other hawkers but power-packed with flavour.

name: Fung Yi Delights Hokkien Mee Orh Luak
description: Hidden gem that serves up solid plate of Hokkien Mee with 3 types of noodles - yellow noodles, thick and thin vermicelli. Nice texture and significant amount of seafood. Paired with chin cha lok chilli sauce.

name: Uncle Peter Hokkien Mee
description: Uncle Peter's version has a semi-dry texture, allowing the noodles to soak up the flavours of the prawn stock.
